As of the 2010 census, there were 103 people living in the CDP: 59 male and 44 female. 8 were 19 years old or younger, 12 were ages 20–34, 18 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 27 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 38 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 57.1 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 98.1% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 0.95% [[Race (United States Census)|American Indian]], and 0.95% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]].  5.8% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 57 households in the CDP, 29 family households (50.9%) and 28 non-family households (49.1%), with an average household size of 1.81. Of the family households, 25 were married couples living together, with 1 single-father and 3 single-mother households; the non-family households included 23 adults living alone: 15 male and 8 female.

The CDP contained 158 housing units, of which 57 were occupied and 101 were vacant.<ref name=GR2>{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0436920 |title=American FactFinder: Katherine CDP, Arizona |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=December 2, 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213061306/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0436920 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 }}</ref>

